\
# 1. Overview\
\
## Purpose\
\
The Patient Feedback Module is designed to automate patient follow-ups after treatment, improve patient satisfaction, identify service issues early, collect actionable feedback, and help clinics build a stronger online reputation through ethical Google Review requests.\
\
The module should work seamlessly inside the TheraNet ecosystem without interrupting the therapist's workflow.\
\
---\
\
# 2. Goals\
\
- Improve patient engagement after every visit\
- Automate post-treatment follow-up\
- Measure patient satisfaction\
- Detect unhappy patients early\
- Notify therapists when intervention is required\
- Increase genuine Google Reviews\
- Build long-term patient loyalty\
- Provide analytics for clinic performance\
\
---\
\
# 3. Design Principles\
\
- Automation first\
- Minimal therapist effort\
- Patient-centric communication\
- No spam\
- Google Review policy compliant\
- Modular architecture\
- Multi-clinic ready\
- Mobile-friendly\
- Secure and privacy-focused\
\
---\
\
# 4. User Roles\
\
## Clinic Owner\
\
Permissions\
\
- View all feedback\
- View analytics\
- Configure automation\
- Configure review links\
- Manage templates\
- View therapist performance\
\
---\
\
## Therapist\
\
Permissions\
\
- View patient feedback\
- Respond to complaints\
- Track follow-ups\
- Receive notifications\
\
---\
\
## Receptionist\
\
Permissions\
\
- Monitor pending feedback\
- Contact dissatisfied patients\
- Mark issues resolved\
\
---\
\
## Patient\
\
Permissions\
\
- Submit feedback\
- Leave Google Review\
- Report concerns\
- Update satisfaction\
\
